
Cucumber Review Class 01, January 21, 2020

Cucumber = is framework/Testing tool that supports behavior driven development.
BDD it focuses on end user, oru systme specification they writiten from user perspective.
Acceptance criteria, AC is being written by business analyst.

other tools that support BDD = Serenity, SpecFlow.
Cucumber uses plain language = gherkin language.
Given - pre condition
When - action
Then - result
And - continue any step
but - this is used very rare

Feature: is functionality we are testing, high level feature/functionality of the system,
description of the software feature that we are testing.

Scenario:it is a way how we can test this particular feature or particular fucntionality,
there coudl be multiple scenarios, multiple ways how we can test this particular feature or
functionality fo the system.
Scenario Outline: - executes same scenario muliple times base don the data provided in Examples table

Cucumber datatable - execute same STEP multiple times based on data inside cucumber datatable.


Cucumber datatable

If data becomes large -- > we need to use Excel



==============

what we have in feature file by default
#Author: your.email@your.domain.com
#Keywords Summary :
#Feature: List of scenarios.
#Scenario: Business rule through list of steps with arguments.
#Given: Some precondition step
#When: Some key actions
#Then: To observe outcomes or validation
#And,But: To enumerate more Given,When,Then steps
#Scenario Outline: List of steps for data-driven as an Examples and <placeholder>
#Examples: Container for s table
#Background: List of steps run before each of the scenarios
#""" (Doc Strings)
#| (Data Tables)
#@ (Tags/Labels):To group Scenarios
#<> (placeholder)
#""
## (Comments)
#Sample Feature Definition Template

Background = will work only for particular feature, but for all scenarios with all common steps
Hooks = more global concept that is applicable for all the scenarios.



